        <briefdescription>
<para>Spawn the server and block until its TCP port accepts connections. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The server is launched with <computeroutput>--port &lt;opts.port&gt;</computeroutput> so the port is authoritative from the caller&apos;s side regardless of <computeroutput>server-config.json</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>opts</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Launch options. <computeroutput>opts.exe</computeroutput> must exist.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A ready-to-use <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_managed_server" kindref="compound">ManagedServer</ref>.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="exception"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TryllError</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>If the executable is not found, the process fails to start, the process exits before the port opens, or <computeroutput>opts.startTimeout</computeroutput> expires. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
